        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 6:38AM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 638 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 31 miles northwest of Manchester to 20
miles northwest of Pleasant Grove, or extending from 45 miles
northwest of Clarksville to 22 miles northwest of Winnsboro, moving
east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant, Clarksville, Boxelder, Hagansport, Idabel, Mount
Vernon, Bogata, Bagwell, Manchester, Wilkerson, Wright City,
Valliant, Detroit, Winfield, Talco, Avery, Millerton, Annona,
Garvin and Miller's Cove.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
